WINGADD
  Assign planes to a wing letter, so the wing can be used as a group
  designation on bomb and fly missions.

SYNTAX
  wingadd <wing-letter> <plane-spec>[?realm=N][&type=X]
  wing    <wing-letter> <plane-spec>[?realm=N][&type=X]

DESCRIPTION
  Sets the wing letter on every owned plane matching <plane-spec>.
  Once planes carry a wing letter, that same letter can be used as
  the plane-spec argument to 'bomb' or 'fly' to select every plane
  currently in that wing — no need to track individual uids.

  <wing-letter> - a single letter a-z or A-Z naming the wing, or
                  "~" to clear the wing assignment (return the
                  planes to the null/unassigned wing)
  <plane-spec>  - which planes to (re)assign:
                    "*"        every owned plane
                    "5"        plane uid 5
                    "0-5"      plane uids 0 through 5
                    "2,14,23"  a comma list of uids
                    "~"        every plane with no wing assigned
                    "c"        every plane currently in wing c
                               (lets you rename/merge a wing)

  <plane-spec> also accepts the same ?realm=N/&type=X suffix filters
  as 'plane' (see 'info plane'/'info realm'):
    ?realm=N    only planes currently within realm N's bounding box
    ?type=X     only planes of type X -- matches the short type code
                (e.g. "f35") or a substring of the full name

  Wing assignment has no effect on efficiency, mobility, or combat —
  it is purely an organizational grouping.

EXAMPLE
  wingadd c *                put all owned planes into wing c
  wingadd b 0-5              put planes 0-5 into wing b
  wingadd d ~                put all unassigned planes into wing d
  wingadd e c                rename/merge wing c's planes into wing e
  wingadd ~ c                clear wing c's planes back to unassigned
  wingadd e *?realm=2&type=f35   put your F-35s in realm 2 into wing e
  bomb c 4,2 s               bomb sector 4,2 with every plane in wing c
  fly c -3,1                 fly every plane in wing c to -3,1

